1
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:16,980
Let's meet up. There's something I want to tell you. Call me when you get home.

2
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:21,610
What does he want to say to me? At this time?

3
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,350
Why do you sound like that? Is something wrong?

4
00:00:25,350 --> 00:00:27,790
No.

5
00:00:30,110 --> 00:00:32,200
I just want to see you.

6
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:36,340
If he wants to see me, my heart is still wavering.

7
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:38,800
Like a fool.

8
00:01:43,940 --> 00:01:46,390
Yun! Wake up, Yun!

9
00:01:46,390 --> 00:01:49,530
Yun! Please get up. Yun!

10
00:01:49,530 --> 00:01:51,460
What should I do?

11
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:56,610
Please wake up.

12
00:01:56,610 --> 00:02:01,610
Unni. Unni, help me... Yun is bleeding.

13
00:02:01,610 --> 00:02:05,070
Yun, wake up!

14
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:10,320
I Wanna Hear Your Song

15
00:02:12,610 --> 00:02:15,470
Episode 17

16
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:57,280
What happened for you to drink so much?

17
00:02:57,280 --> 00:03:03,820
Maestro Nam, Did you change the passcode because of me?

18
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:07,740
Because I might do whatever I want?

19
00:03:08,450 --> 00:03:14,330
Nam Ju Wan. You're too much.

20
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:18,840
So cruel.

21
00:03:29,090 --> 00:03:33,440
Why did you drink past your limit? You can't even drink.

22
00:03:35,210 --> 00:03:38,520
Only you know.

23
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:42,770
Everyone else thinks I have a high tolerance.

24
00:03:42,770 --> 00:03:48,260
So they keep giving me drinks. And I keep drinking them.

25
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:55,290
I'm being childish, but let me ask you something.

26
00:03:55,290 --> 00:04:01,330
What am I to you? A junior?

27
00:04:01,330 --> 00:04:07,080
A colleague? A person you sleep with when you need someone?

28
00:04:08,490 --> 00:04:11,780
What kind of question is that? So childish.

29
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:16,760
I know. I keep getting more childish.

30
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:22,970
I know already. You have no interest in Hong Yi Yeong.

31
00:04:22,970 --> 00:04:29,400
But I can understand why you keep looking out for her.

32
00:04:35,470 --> 00:04:39,020
How long do I have to wait this time?

33
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:43,060
Tell me.

34
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:45,800
One month?

35
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:48,590
One year?

36
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:53,950
I can wait as long as I have to. Really.

37
00:04:54,720 --> 00:05:00,630
Why should you have to wait for me? Don't do that anymore.

38
00:05:03,590 --> 00:05:08,620
Why? You don't even like Hong Yi Yeong.

39
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:11,430
This is not a problem about Hong Yi Yeong. It's about you and me.

40
00:05:11,430 --> 00:05:15,540
What problem?

41
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:19,710
All this time, we've been fine with no problem.

42
00:05:19,710 --> 00:05:24,810
We just avoided the problems. You're also bored.

43
00:05:24,810 --> 00:05:29,450
You don't like that it's unclear whether you are a friend or colleague or lover. Am I wrong?

44
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:33,600
What's that supposed to mean?

45
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,950
Are you telling me to stay away from you?

46
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:42,260
You're wasting your time waiting for me. I'm being sincere.

47
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:46,110
Don't make me laugh.

48
00:05:46,110 --> 00:05:49,290
You're saying we should break up.

49
00:05:51,140 --> 00:05:55,570
Why are you like this to me? How could you?

50
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:26,440
Are you awake? When did you wake up?

51
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:31,160
- A little while ago.
- I didn't even know.

52
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:35,900
Did you bring me here?

53
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:43,430
You said you would come but didn't come. You said to call but didn't pick up.

54
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:48,120
I got nervous and searched for you, and found you in an alley.

55
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:54,220
What happened? Did something happen?

56
00:06:55,480 --> 00:07:01,670
That girl stabbed your younger brother. I saw everything.

57
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:07,510
Kill me here. Kill me! I said to kill me!

58
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:21,170
No, there was nothing.

59
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:24,410
Yeah, right.

60
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:27,210
You got hurt here.

61
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:36,380
The doctor said it would have been bad if you were hit anywhere else. You're lucky.

62
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:40,840
I won't go that easily. My head is so thick.

63
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:50,330
Don't think too much and rest. I'll stay here.

64
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:54,350
You're being affectionate because I was hurt. Yi Yeong.

65
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:14,040
Did you get some sleep? Probably not.

66
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:18,090
I met his doctor, and the trauma therapy went well, so there won't be any serious issues.

67
00:08:18,090 --> 00:08:21,580
Go home. Wash up and go to work.

68
00:08:22,550 --> 00:08:25,980
- I'll go a little later.
- If I tell you to go, then go.

69
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:30,780
If you don't go right now, I'm going to tell everything to my parents. Starting from the accident one year ago.

70
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:34,570
- You think I won't?
- I'll leave in time for work.

71
00:08:34,570 --> 00:08:37,640
It's hard enough for me, without you acting like this, Unni.

72
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:42,380
I'll figure things out on my own, so don't worry and go.

73
00:08:42,380 --> 00:08:47,390
What do you know that you'll figure things out on your own? You fool!

74
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:53,380
Sinyeong Philharmonic Orchestra
Maestro Nam Ju Wan's Inauguration Music Festival

75
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:58,300
What is this? I said not to use this cover but you went and used it anyway!

76
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:03,510
You said we couldn't do it for our twentieth anniversary cover, so I think she just used it for his inauguration festival.

77
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:06,880
- Even the Chairwoman approved.
- That's probably because Manager Yun kept praising it,

78
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:11,080
so she just said it's good. You know how her personality is.

79
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:14,720
You offered no resistance, did you?  Where is Manager Yun?

80
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:20,060
Even so, this is what she said. She said the Chairwoman didn't like the picture on the flier

81
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:25,060
and insisted on a re-take. So the manager went there.

82
00:09:25,060 --> 00:09:27,260
What?

83
00:09:28,970 --> 00:09:32,310
I just love this cover.

84
00:09:32,310 --> 00:09:38,130
It suits Nam Ju Wan well. It's unique and futuristic.

85
00:09:38,130 --> 00:09:41,110
This is why I trust you.

86
00:09:41,110 --> 00:09:45,200
What's with the sudden compliment? It's scary.

87
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:49,440
- I appreciate that.
- This ring is like Pontious Pilate's ring.

88
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:53,600
- How childish.
- So this is what it was.

89
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:58,340
I guess he  couldn't  do anything else but give me what he bought for the girl.

90
00:09:58,340 --> 00:10:01,910
I was going to land a good kick, but I stopped myself.

91
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:05,540
When's your vacation?

92
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:08,870
I don't know if I can take it. There's too much happening.

93
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:11,510
You should rest when you should. You're not a worker ant.

94
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:15,440
If I don't have happiness, then it's all completely worthless.

95
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:21,700
What will make you happy. President Go's position?

96
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:27,430
- Not at all.
-  It's not?

97
00:10:27,430 --> 00:10:31,190
But I can't say.

98
00:10:31,190 --> 00:10:35,690
If you use me, I'm used.  If you throw me away. I'm thrown away.

99
00:10:35,690 --> 00:10:38,520
You're all ready.

100
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:43,960
Please make our Chairwoman look the prettiest she can be in the pictures.

101
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:47,700
That sly fox.

102
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:55,360
You're really not going to attend the rehearsal?

103
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:58,960
I'd like to, but I'm afraid I'll interfere with the rehearsal.

104
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:02,510
Why are you being so cautious? It's not like you did something wrong.

105
00:11:02,510 --> 00:11:07,350
I'm not being cautious, I just don't want you to be uncomfortable.

106
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:10,830
Is the mouse being considerate of the cat?

107
00:11:22,010 --> 00:11:24,360
What are you doing?

108
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:26,090
It's alright.

109
00:11:26,090 --> 00:11:28,520
It's my reply I wasn't able to give yesterday.

110
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:34,370
I'm going to watch you carefully.  How long can you last in this orchestra?

111
00:11:42,470 --> 00:11:44,820
Your hand is so hot.

112
00:11:51,770 --> 00:11:53,040
What do you think you're doing?

113
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,080
What did I do?

114
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:58,210
He's our conductor.  How could a musician lay her hands on the Conductor?

115
00:11:58,210 --> 00:11:59,830
What if someone had seen?

116
00:11:59,830 --> 00:12:03,410
You would get fired.  You wouldn't be able to perform anywhere.

117
00:12:03,410 --> 00:12:07,310
You don't know anything, so shut your mouth.  Don't you know that this is all because of you?

118
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:11,440
If you weren't here, then nothing would have happened.  You have ruined everything.

119
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,390
I ruined everything?

120
00:12:12,390 --> 00:12:18,240
Think carefully about the things that happened after you came here.

121
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:21,440
Poodle or whatever.  For the conductor from the start.  Whose ankles have you been hanging onto?

122
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,340
Who demoralized all the orchestra members?

123
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:24,090
That's—

124
00:12:24,090 --> 00:12:27,220
What? Do you feel unfairly wronged?

125
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,160
You shouldn't feel wronged. You made it this way.

126
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:36,100
Do me a favor and leave here.

127
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:41,130
If Maestro Nam gets fired, then it will be your fault too.

128
00:13:05,930 --> 00:13:09,400
I didn't stay here for this to happen.

129
00:13:19,660 --> 00:13:25,680
By working harder, I wanted to become a performer who could make people happy.

130
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:29,790
But I made it difficult for myself and for the man I love.,

131
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:35,150
For my colleagues as well...  I made things difficult for everyone.

132
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:42,800
Do I deserve to be here?

133
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:51,830
Would I be able to hold a mallet again with the hand that stabbed a person?

134
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:04,080
Are these all of Ian's belongings?

135
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:06,190
As of now.

136
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:12,940
There were no cameras in the alley, so I looked through some security cameras nearby.

137
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:16,570
That person started following you after you got out of the taxi.

138
00:14:16,570 --> 00:14:19,520
I couldn't see his face because he was wearing a helmet.

139
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:21,430
You don't have any idea who it could be?

140
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:24,830
Yun Yeong Gil, or someone who doesn't like me.

141
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:28,430
By chance, did you meet Yun Yeong Gil yesterday?

142
00:14:31,430 --> 00:14:33,660
Did you do that?

143
00:14:35,070 --> 00:14:37,700
You've been busy since morning.  How did you find him?

144
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:40,550
If you found him, do you think I couldn't find him?

145
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,260
This guy is dangerous.

146
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:47,390
If you were going to meet him, you should have told me first.

147
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:50,610
I didn't have time to do that.  I was feeling impatient.

148
00:14:51,830 --> 00:14:56,940
You were lucky this time.  You could have died from a cerebral hemorrhage.

149
00:14:56,940 --> 00:15:01,630
Stay quite for now until I find out if it was him or someone else.

150
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:04,370
If not, I'm going to tell the CEO everything.

151
00:15:05,130 --> 00:15:07,200
Stop nagging.

152
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,110
Leave now.

153
00:15:15,140 --> 00:15:17,570
You said it was Hong Yi Yeong who found you yesterday.

154
00:15:17,570 --> 00:15:19,890
Yes.

155
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:25,300
It that was fate, it was ill-fated... you two have a rough connection.

156
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:42,550
That person...

157
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:47,580
Jang Yun, Male

158
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:55,670
Why are you at the hospital today, when it's not your appointment day?

159
00:15:56,390 --> 00:15:58,980
Hello, Doctor!

160
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:01,700
- It's been too long, hasn't it?
- Shhhhhh!

161
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:04,150
Have you been well? What, what, what?

162
00:16:04,150 --> 00:16:05,130
What's wrong? What's wrong?

163
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:07,920
Doctor, Doctor, wait a minute.

164
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:12,300
Why are you at the hospital?  You don't have an appointment today.

165
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:14,050
My friend is in the hospital.

166
00:16:14,050 --> 00:16:16,920
Who's your friend?

167
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:19,310
You gave up your crutches.

168
00:16:19,310 --> 00:16:20,620
Don't change the subject.

169
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:24,450
By chance, do you know Jang Yun?

170
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:28,950
Jang Yun? I don't know anyone by that name.

171
00:16:28,950 --> 00:16:32,740
I just saw you come from his ward.

172
00:16:32,740 --> 00:16:34,560
You must have seen wrong.

173
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:38,200
What's your friend's name? I'm going to confirm it.

174
00:16:40,540 --> 00:16:41,810
What is it?

175
00:16:41,810 --> 00:16:45,880
You've become prettier.  Has something good happened to you?

176
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:50,340
Are you joking? I didn't sleep a wink.

177
00:16:51,860 --> 00:16:55,200
Doctor, you're much prettier when you get angry.

178
00:17:04,190 --> 00:17:06,440
- This weekend?
- Yes.

179
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:10,410
Your uncle is coming home on Friday, so let's have a meal together this weekend.

180
00:17:10,410 --> 00:17:13,970
He wrote down a ton of things that he wanted to eat in his notebook.

181
00:17:13,970 --> 00:17:17,200
As he gets older, he has become more of a glutton.

182
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,500
Oh, that's right. About your conductor.

183
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:23,790
Can you bring him home with you on that day?

184
00:17:23,790 --> 00:17:26,970
I'm indebted to him from what he did for me that day.

185
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:30,090
I want to cook a meal for him.

186
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:32,670
The Conductor?

187
00:17:32,670 --> 00:17:38,070
He probably can't, since he's a busy person.  It's hard for him to make time.

188
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,120
Is that so?

189
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:46,270
Then, by chance, would it be alright if I called him?

190
00:17:46,270 --> 00:17:49,950
I got his number that day.

191
00:17:49,950 --> 00:17:53,660
No, Aunt, I'll ask him.

192
00:17:53,660 --> 00:17:58,090
I understand. I'll talk to him about it.

193
00:18:06,330 --> 00:18:11,480
On such a good day...

194
00:18:16,130 --> 00:18:18,430
What are you doing here, Conductor?

195
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:21,400
What did you do to Jang Yun?

196
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:24,560
What are you talking about out of the blue?

197
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:27,450
You should start from the beginning, so I can understand you.

198
00:18:27,450 --> 00:18:32,640
He was hurt and hospitalized yesterday.  I found out that someone hit him on the head.

199
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:40,880
Are you trying to say that I did it?

200
00:18:42,090 --> 00:18:44,260
Why would I do something that murderous?

201
00:18:44,260 --> 00:18:47,670
Please don't do anything useless.

202
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:52,130
You bastard!

203
00:18:52,130 --> 00:18:55,320
Anything useless? Are you threatening me right now?

204
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:58,310
What about last year? I know what you did on that day.

205
00:18:58,310 --> 00:19:02,270
It's all because of you!  If you didn't do something pointless...

206
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:05,180
Kim Ian wouldn't have died.

207
00:19:05,180 --> 00:19:07,540
What are you saying now?

208
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:10,870
Are you trying to say that I killed Kim Ian?

209
00:19:10,870 --> 00:19:15,590
Then report me.  Should we go to the police station right now?

210
00:19:18,450 --> 00:19:21,810
I'm about to go crazy.  Why is our Conductor acting this way lately?

211
00:19:21,810 --> 00:19:24,230
Why are you so anxious?

212
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:27,780
Is it because of Jang Yun?  What's going to happen if we fight among ourselves?

213
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:30,410
We've been in the same boat for a long time.

214
00:19:30,410 --> 00:19:34,740
I've never been in the same boat as you.  I just wanted to conduct!

215
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:37,670
You are the professor who used his poor student, who was desperate for money to study abroad.

216
00:19:37,670 --> 00:19:39,570
You're the one who laundered money.

217
00:19:39,570 --> 00:19:43,780
That's why... that's why I gave you what you wanted!

218
00:19:43,780 --> 00:19:46,900
Is it reasonable at your age to have a permanent position with the Sinyeong Philharmonic?

219
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:49,090
What about you, Professor?

220
00:19:49,090 --> 00:19:51,720
Did being Sinyeong Group's son-in-law put your mind at peace?

221
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:54,140
I'm anxious beccause I don't know when I'll get kicked out.

222
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:57,350
And neither do you, Professor.

223
00:20:02,130 --> 00:20:04,350
That bastard!

224
00:20:42,670 --> 00:20:47,340
Look, when you do this, doesn't it seem like you're holding hands with Hyung?

225
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,630
So, you don't have to be scared.

226
00:20:53,630 --> 00:20:57,350
Because you and I are here together.

227
00:21:03,010 --> 00:21:06,420
Do you know what I regret the most right now?

228
00:21:06,420 --> 00:21:08,190
There's something you regret?

229
00:21:08,190 --> 00:21:10,260
While he was alive, I never...

230
00:21:10,260 --> 00:21:14,790
I never held his hand, except for when we were young.

231
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:57,150
Aunt

232
00:22:08,010 --> 00:22:09,700
The person you are trying to reach is unavailable.

233
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:13,160
Ah, why isn't this bastard answering the phone?

234
00:22:14,910 --> 00:22:17,040
You surprised me!

235
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:24,360
I told you not to come looking for me at school.

236
00:22:25,150 --> 00:22:26,240
What happened to your face?

237
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:28,780
I got hit.

238
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:31,810
Buy me a cup of coffee.

239
00:22:43,020 --> 00:22:46,700
Hey, did you know that Ian had an older brother?

240
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:49,580
Yes, I did.

241
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:51,950
I saw him at the trial.

242
00:22:51,950 --> 00:22:57,420
I couldn't forget the look in his eyes. I guess that's how he remembered me.

243
00:22:57,420 --> 00:23:00,790
You little... Why didn't you tell me that?

244
00:23:00,790 --> 00:23:05,960
You don't tell me everything either, so why would I?

245
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:07,770
Jeez.

246
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:11,250
Did you search for him?

247
00:23:11,250 --> 00:23:13,540
No, it was the other way around.

248
00:23:13,540 --> 00:23:18,070
I was watching Hong Yi Young and he suddenly appeared.

249
00:23:18,860 --> 00:23:25,620
He lives close to Hong Yi Young. It seems like he found her on purpose.

250
00:23:25,620 --> 00:23:29,650
Tell me more.

251
00:23:29,650 --> 00:23:33,400
He seems to know a lot.

252
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:36,180
He even offered up money.

253
00:23:38,220 --> 00:23:43,330
He is very curious about who is helping me and what I'm looking for.

254
00:23:43,330 --> 00:23:46,200
So, I did some thinking.

255
00:23:47,170 --> 00:23:51,800
I was thinking about who I should go to first when I find that missing object.

256
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:55,700
Are you doing this because you need more money?

257
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:58,190
You hit him on the head, didn't you?

258
00:23:58,980 --> 00:24:03,710
Professor, I'm someone who give as much as he gets.

259
00:24:03,710 --> 00:24:09,170
If you hit me, I hit you.  If you step on me, I step on you.

260
00:24:10,370 --> 00:24:15,080
So, it's correct that I hit him.

261
00:24:18,010 --> 00:24:20,200
That's my locker number.

262
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:24,480
A bank account is a headache. I'll will  look tomorrow.

263
00:24:27,140 --> 00:24:29,840
Bastard.

264
00:24:51,140 --> 00:24:53,110
Would you like me to feed you?

265
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:57,020
What?

266
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:13,400
Now. Open.

267
00:25:17,370 --> 00:25:19,570
I guess you don't want me to do it.

268
00:25:30,890 --> 00:25:32,520
Why?

269
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:34,880
That totally doesn't match you.

270
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:36,620
Give it.

271
00:25:39,630 --> 00:25:43,460
Is it okay? Is it tasty?

272
00:25:47,670 --> 00:25:50,020
It seems you cooked it.

273
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:55,700
What do you mean by that? Is it strange-tasting?

274
00:25:59,020 --> 00:26:03,470
This is... I salted it because it was too bland... but...

275
00:26:03,470 --> 00:26:05,130
Don't eat it. I'll make it again.

276
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:09,500
No, no.  It's fine. Fine.  I'll eat anything. It's okay.

277
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:12,630
Anyway it's way better-tasting than hospital food.

278
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:28,800
How did you day go?  Everything was okay at the rehearsal?

279
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:34,010
Of course not. Same old, same old. No particular problems.

280
00:26:34,010 --> 00:26:36,700
Everyone is worried about you.

281
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:39,390
Principal oboeist Hwang asked if it's alright to visit you?

282
00:26:39,390 --> 00:26:46,000
Principal Oboist Hwang?  Make a visit?   Making a fuss for nothing.

283
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:51,100
Anyway, you're so warped.  Fine. I'm close with the orchestra members.

284
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:56,500
Will you come with her?

285
00:26:56,590 --> 00:26:58,020
Naturally.

286
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:02,900
In that case... I'll put up with it. Even though it's a bother.

287
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:09,400
- Have you always been such a smooth talker?
- What are you saying?

288
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:14,330
Speaking so nicely that I itch all over.

289
00:27:14,330 --> 00:27:16,930
Didn't you know? I've always been good at talking.

290
00:27:16,930 --> 00:27:18,560
Liar.

291
00:27:19,810 --> 00:27:22,540
A big one.

292
00:27:31,500 --> 00:27:34,230
You said in the summer it's a triangle.

293
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:40,510
That's the constellation Ian was looking for. It's easy to find.

294
00:27:45,590 --> 00:27:48,680
I can't see it because it's cloudy.

295
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:51,880
You'll find it on a clear day.

296
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:56,390
The three summer stars are Vega, Deneb, and Altair.

297
00:27:56,390 --> 00:28:00,520
You know  that Altair the Herdsman, and Vega, the Weaver, are meeting?

298
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:04,030
Ah, you mean the ones meeting on the seventh day of the seventh month?

299
00:28:04,030 --> 00:28:06,990
Ian really liked them.

300
00:28:06,990 --> 00:28:10,610
Hey, so unsophisticated.  What's to like about that? But he did.

301
00:28:10,610 --> 00:28:13,370
He said he liked the feeling of looking forward to someone.

302
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:17,880
"We look forward for a whole year, and then we meet for just one day."

303
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:21,330
"So sad. Isn't that great, Hyung?"

304
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:28,200
Ian was like that, although you've probably forgotten all that.

305
00:28:35,690 --> 00:28:41,390
Yesterday, I said I had something to tell you.

306
00:28:41,390 --> 00:28:43,520
Yes.

307
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:46,830
Actually, for a long time,

308
00:28:48,180 --> 00:28:51,060
I hated you.

309
00:28:51,060 --> 00:28:53,750
For a whole year, every day.

310
00:29:01,330 --> 00:29:05,070
I thought you were lying

311
00:29:05,970 --> 00:29:09,500
when you said you couldn't remember what happened last year.

312
00:29:09,500 --> 00:29:13,720
I'd been hearing about you for the three months of last summer from Ian.

313
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:18,060
You. The one who said she didn't know he had died and the reasons why he died and

314
00:29:18,060 --> 00:29:21,930
was living well and unscathed,

315
00:29:21,930 --> 00:29:25,410
by using the excuse that she couldn't remember.

316
00:29:26,430 --> 00:29:28,700
I couldn't forgive that person.

317
00:29:34,830 --> 00:29:38,950
Everytime you said you liked me, I thought.

318
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:43,870
What kind of feeling does this woman, whom my brother loved,

319
00:29:43,870 --> 00:29:47,500
who has forgotten his very existence, have for me?

320
00:29:50,650 --> 00:29:52,540
But then...

321
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:59,120
even if you are right that you shouldn't be forgiven even if I die,

322
00:30:01,370 --> 00:30:04,020
I found I kept on thinking about you.

323
00:30:08,230 --> 00:30:12,830
When I first met you, I found you weren't the person I had imagined.

324
00:30:12,830 --> 00:30:19,550
An affection unlike myself came over me one day.

325
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:31,100
I kept turning away from it. I felt I was going crazy.

326
00:30:33,220 --> 00:30:38,520
"This isn't what I want."   I was sorry about everything.

327
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:41,300
I didn't want to admit it.

328
00:30:41,300 --> 00:30:45,020
The day you went to the warehouse by yourself,

329
00:30:48,060 --> 00:30:50,820
I barely admitted it.

330
00:30:51,970 --> 00:30:55,420
Even if it's true

331
00:30:56,660 --> 00:30:59,860
that you stabbed Ian,

332
00:31:02,140 --> 00:31:04,930
I can't help it.

333
00:31:07,670 --> 00:31:11,930
I just have to go along with my honest feeling.

334
00:31:13,390 --> 00:31:19,420
Now that I'm here,  in front of you,...

335
00:31:27,660 --> 00:31:29,990
what should I do now?

336
00:31:48,490 --> 00:31:53,210
So what is that?

337
00:31:53,300 --> 00:31:58,900
Saehaeda... no. Saehaeradi?

338
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:02,650
It's Scheherazade. Did you watch until the end?

339
00:32:02,700 --> 00:32:06,200
- Wasn't it good to watch me like that?
- Good? Are you nuts?

340
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:12,800
You're not it. Saehaera whatever is like listening to god's music.

341
00:32:12,850 --> 00:32:18,260
This old body is itching all over wanting to be in love.

342
00:32:18,260 --> 00:32:22,930
Wow, that's great, Ms. Bok Bun! That's what this music is about, love.

343
00:32:22,930 --> 00:32:25,700
Is that it?

344
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:30,720
By the way,  is the go-fer doing well?

345
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:36,980
The go-fer? She does well as always.

346
00:32:36,980 --> 00:32:40,200
Did you two fight?

347
00:32:41,190 --> 00:32:43,730
I can't fight with her.

348
00:32:45,970 --> 00:32:49,150
Don't waste your energy is useless arguments.

349
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:55,400
Just swing your baton harder and make your name worthy.

350
00:32:55,400 --> 00:33:01,900
Isn't this your first concert?

351
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:09,400
From this country floor, by crawling through the mud, you managed

352
00:33:09,430 --> 00:33:12,140
to get all the way there.

353
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:15,520
You can't be embarrassed from the start.

354
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:18,940
Even  other people don't know, I know everything.

355
00:33:18,940 --> 00:33:25,420
While shedding bloody tears that no one knows about, you've worked so hard.

356
00:33:26,570 --> 00:33:28,830
I will do well.

357
00:33:28,830 --> 00:33:33,490
I won't be embarrassed. I am your grandson.

358
00:33:33,500 --> 00:33:36,150
Right. That's what you should do.

359
00:33:36,150 --> 00:33:41,100
I'm getting sleepy. I'm going to bed.

360
00:33:41,130 --> 00:33:46,360
You too.  Stop drinking and go to bed. Sleep.

361
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:48,560
Bye.

362
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:04,320
Hello.

363
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:07,430
Hey there. It's the conductor, right?

364
00:34:07,430 --> 00:34:12,910
It's rude of me to call so late. I'm Yi Yeong's aunt.

365
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:26,680
Did I wake you? I'm sorry.

366
00:34:30,110 --> 00:34:31,750
What is it?

367
00:34:32,470 --> 00:34:38,160
Just... It's weird that I feel so relaxed.

368
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:41,690
It's the first time since Ian died.

369
00:34:48,770 --> 00:34:53,180
Until I fall asleep, sing to me.

370
00:34:53,180 --> 00:34:55,210
Sing to you?

371
00:34:56,020 --> 00:34:58,720
It's better than my singing.

372
00:35:01,100 --> 00:35:03,500
- Ten thousand won for ten minutes.
- I'll pay after you sing.

373
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:05,680
After?

374
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:08,850
Deal.

375
00:35:15,370 --> 00:35:19,340
♫ This exciting day.

376
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:26,050
♫ This day. Beautiful day.

377
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:35,290
♫ My heart was trembling so. My heart was trembling so.

378
00:35:35,290 --> 00:35:40,880
♫ For a while it was beating so,

379
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:44,680
♫ On that bright day

380
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:51,030
♫ That day. Beautiful day.

381
00:35:51,030 --> 00:35:57,250
♫ A happy day loving you.

382
00:35:57,250 --> 00:36:00,800
♫ To be loving you.

383
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:05,190
♫ I'm gonna love you.

384
00:36:06,730 --> 00:36:11,990
♫ An exciting day ♫

385
00:36:11,990 --> 00:36:16,390
♫ Beautiful day ♫

386
00:36:17,150 --> 00:36:21,840
♫ A happy day.  ♫

387
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:25,120
♫ To be loving you ♫

388
00:36:26,350 --> 00:36:30,070
♫ I'm gonna love you ♫
